On the other hand, Vitro is to blame for his difficult situation from 2008 onwards in the context of the major economic crisis in the United States that struck the country.
For this reason, the González Sada family objected to the same court of appeal so that the vote would be taken in plenary, i.e. by all judges, because only three of them voted.
